race.comment: THE KILL CLUB (13) was quickly in form, beaten a neck over 1000m at Warrnambool. She's further improved and fitter again is suitably placed to go one better. FLITGROVE (6) resumes and will be hard to stop if presented on song. Her two Flemington jumpout wins suggest she will be, and she was last seen in much stronger at Caulfield. SHOOTER MCGAVIN (4) resumes and has jumped out at Flemington. He has been racing over longer sprints but positions forward and gets in well this grade with the 3kg claim. No surprise to see him race well. SOMAURUM (16) spiked her figures, beaten a whisker over 1000m at Dunkeld. She can't be ruled out on that effort, and the rails barrier should advantage.
